Comment.MultiLanguageText: MC_MoveRelative: Start job with a positive edge
MC_MoveAbsolute: Start job with a positive edge
Direction of absolute movement: 0: Positive direction / 1: Negative direction / 3: Shortest direction
0: Non position-controlled operation / 1: Position-controlled mode - The parameter applies as long as the MC_MoveJog command is executed. After this, the setting of MC_Power applies again.
MC_Halt: Start job with a positive edge

Acceleration control: False: The current acceleration at the start of the job is reduced using the configured jerk. Afterwards, the deceleration builds up / True: The acceleration is set to 0.0 at the start of the job, and the deceleration immediately builds up.
The job was aborted by another job during execution (see also StatusID)
An error occurred during execution of the job. The job is rejected. The cause of the error can be found in the "ErrorID" parameter.
ErrorID of motion control instruction (see also StatusID)
Additional specification of affected Motion control instruction of CommandAborted or Error: 0: No instruction / 1: MC_MoveRelative / 2: MC_MoveAbsolute / 3: MC_Halt
